Actress Idia Aisien has recounted how her family pressured her into rejecting a Range Rover automobile gift from an unknown fan. The 30-year-old actress revealed that she was forced to sell the vehicle for peace to reign with her family. In a recent Podcast hosted by Stephanie Coker, she said: “Two years ago I got a Range Rover from someone I never knew. It was somebody that chatted me on Instagram. He had planned with my followers, people I knew and my friends.” Continuing, Aisien said: “Inside the Range Rover, there was Champaign, teddy bear, cake and flowers. I thought it was very thoughtful.”   Actor Nosa Rex loses dad     Kwankwaso, myself are architects of modern Kano, says…     Gunmen kill two policemen, raze station in Imo   According to her, it would be the first time a man would offer her such a gifts but her parent declined. - Advertisement - “The point is not that it was a car but that I had never gotten anything before even when I had a boyfriend. “Sadly, my family didn’t allow me to keep the Range Rover. So, I asked him(Giver) if he wanted it back. He didn’t want it back, so I ended up selling it, I never kept it,” she said. On whether she saved the money made from the sale of the car, the ‘Bad Boys and Bridemaid’star said yes. “Yes. He didn’t want it back. What was I supposed to do?” SPONSORED